article.headline: Princeton 86, Siena 77
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. -- Kareem Maddox scored 30 points and grabbed 10 rebounds to help Princeton defeat Siena 86-77 in overtime on Sunday. Dan Mavraides chipped in 19 points for the Tigers (3-3), including a 3-pointer to tie it at 69 with 1 second left in regulation. Princeton held the Saints (2-4) to 3-of-12 shooting (25 percent) in the extra period, including 0 for 5 from 3-point range. The Tigers were 11 of 14 from the free-throw line (78.6 percent) and 3 of 4 from the field (75 percent), with their lone miss coming from long range, after regulation. Siena cut it to 80-77 with 31 seconds left in overtime but the Tigers responded by going 6 for 6 from the free-throw line the rest of the way. Ryan Rossiter had 21 rebounds and 14 points for the Saints. Siena also got 16 points from Clarence Jackson, 15 from Owen Wignot and 14 from OD Anosike.
